 all flows. No outlet pool and 0.11 m drop onto rocks likely an impediment to both juveniles and adults. The calculated water velocity is 0.07 m/s. CO fry captured. Water is diverted upstream of Hwy 8 for irrigation purposes during the growing season and regulated by a manual irrigation gate. Most water was diverted during the assessment. Mr. Miller observed CO spawning upstream of Hwy 8 after the gate was opened in the fall.</span></p></td><td class="cl-00929321"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa">http://a100.gov.bc.ca/pub/pscismap/imageViewer.do?assessmentId=200143</span></p></td></tr><tr style="overflow-wrap:break-word;"><td class="cl-00929322"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa">1024713603</span></p></td><td class="cl-00929323"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa"></span></p></td><td class="cl-00929324"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa">Skuhun Creek</span></p></td><td class="cl-0092932a"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa">mouth</span></p></td><td class="cl-0092932b"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa">Other</span></p></td><td class="cl-0092932c"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa">No</span></p></td><td class="cl-0092932d"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa">n/a</span></p></td><td class="cl-00929334"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa"></span></p></td><td class="cl-00929335"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa"></span></p></td><td class="cl-0092933e"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa">High</span></p></td><td class="cl-0092933f"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa"></span></p></td><td class="cl-00929340"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa">Post-rehabilitation monitoring</span></p></td><td class="cl-00929348"><p class="cl-00927cc8"><span class="cl-008f7ffa">Mouth of river was perched above Nicola River following 2021 Atmospheric River, preventing fish from accessing. </span></p></td><td class="cl-